    The disadvantages of tourism in Abha are overcrowding, lack of parking in parks, and lack of restaurants in tourist places.
    <br>
    <br>

    <span style="font-size: 30px;"> 2. Rijal Almaa</span><br>
    There are many places in Rijal Almaa such as Wadi Haswa, and Al Kharafi is always green all the time with thick thick fog, Rijal Almaa Heritage Village, which dates back to 1331, Kasbah Al Aws is one of the most important tourist places in Rijal Almaa, as it was used for purposes  Military and defense.  The disadvantages of Rijal Almaa tourism are rough and narrow roads, few restaurants and few hotels.
    <br>
    <br>


    <span style="font-size: 30px;"> 3.Mahayil Asir</span><br>
    As for the tourist places in Mihail Asir, they are represented in Al-Shallal Park, Al-Hilla Volcanic Park, Hili Valley and Al-Faisaliah Park.  Disadvantages of tourism in Mahayil Asir have been reported in a few restaurants, and there is no amusement park.
    <br>
    <br>


    <span style="font-size: 30px;"> 4.Al-Namas</span><br>
    Al-Namas is one of the governorates of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, located in the Asir region of Saudi Arabia, and is located on the Sarawat mountain range. The city of Al-Namas is called the “Switzerland of the Arabian Peninsula” because of its beautiful landscapes and a calm and relaxing atmosphere, medical tourism is available in some seasons and many recreational services.     
     <br>
